tests.fullTitle: math odds with 2 random devices
tests.code:
const d4 = new math_1.RandomDevice([
    [1, new math_1.Fraction(1, 4)],
    [2, new math_1.Fraction(1, 4)],
    [3, new math_1.Fraction(1, 4)],
    [4, new math_1.Fraction(1, 4)],
]);
const abcDie = new math_1.RandomDevice([
    ["a", new math_1.Fraction(1, 3)],
    ["b", new math_1.Fraction(1, 3)],
    ["c", new math_1.Fraction(1, 3)],
]);
const expected = [
    { value: [1, "a"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
    { value: [1, "b"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
    { value: [1, "c"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
    { value: [2, "a"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
    { value: [2, "b"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
    { value: [2, "c"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
    { value: [3, "a"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
    { value: [3, "b"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
    { value: [3, "c"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
    { value: [4, "a"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
    { value: [4, "b"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
    { value: [4, "c"], oddsOfValue: new math_1.Fraction(1, 12) },
];
const results = math_1.odds([d4, abcDie]);
support_1.compareToExpected(chai_1.expect, expected, results, support_1.arraysOfOutcomesAreSame);

tests.title: should have consistent order
tests.fullTitle: Oath domain model Defense dice faces should have consistent order
tests.code:
const someFaces = [
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.DOUBLE,
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.TWO_SHIELDS,
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.SHIELD,
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.TWO_SHIELDS,
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.BLANK,
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.SHIELD,
];
const expected = [
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.BLANK,
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.SHIELD,
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.SHIELD,
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.TWO_SHIELDS,
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.TWO_SHIELDS,
    oath_1.DefenseDieFace.DOUBLE,
];
chai_1.expect(someFaces.sort()).to.deep.equal(expected);

tests.title: can be used to sort results by attack descending, then defense ascending then kill ascending
tests.fullTitle: Oath domain model CampaignResult campaignResultCompareFn can be used to sort results by attack descending, then defense ascending then kill ascending
tests.code:
const someResults = [
    { attack: 5, defense: 2, kill: 0 },
    { attack: 5, defense: 2, kill: 0 },
    { attack: 3, defense: 0, kill: 2 },
    { attack: 4, defense: 4, kill: 0 },
    { attack: 5, defense: 3, kill: 3 },
    { attack: 5, defense: 1, kill: 0 },
    { attack: 5, defense: 1, kill: 2 },
];
const expected = [
    { attack: 5, defense: 1, kill: 0 },
    { attack: 5, defense: 1, kill: 2 },
    { attack: 5, defense: 2, kill: 0 },
    { attack: 5, defense: 2, kill: 0 },
    { attack: 5, defense: 3, kill: 3 },
    { attack: 4, defense: 4, kill: 0 },
    { attack: 3, defense: 0, kill: 2 },
];
chai_1.expect(someResults.sort(oath_1.campaignResultCompareFn)).to.deep.equal(expected);
